All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractCommand
An abstract class that implements the Command interface and provides basic functionality for all commands.
AddElement
The AddElement class represents a command that adds a new worker element to the collection.
AddElementIfMin
The AddElementIfMin class represents a command that adds a new worker element to the collection if its salary is less than the salary of all the elements in the collection.
Clear
The Clear class represents a command that clears the collection.
CollectionControl
The CollectionControl class manages a collection of Worker objects and provides methods for manipulating and accessing the data.
Command
 
CommandControl
The CommandControl class is responsible for mapping commands and storing them in a HashMap for easy access.
CommunicationControl
The CommunicationControl class provides methods for communicating with the user through the console.
Console
A class that represents a console for interacting with the program.
Coordinates
The Coordinates class represents the coordinates of a location.
EmptyInputException
This exception is thrown when the user provides empty input where it is not allowed.
ExecuteScript
The ExecuteScript class represents a command to execute a script file.
Exit
The Exit class extends the AbstractCommand class and represents a command that terminates the program.
FileControl
The FileControl class provides methods to read and write files related to worker information
FilterGreaterStatus
The FilterGreaterStatus class represents a command that filters the elements in the collection by the status field and displays those whose value is greater than the specified one.
GroupByStatus
This command groups the elements of the collection by the value of the status field and displays the number of elements in each group.
Help
The Help command displays the list of available commands and their descriptions.
Info
Command to display information about the collection.
InputException
This exception is thrown when there is an error with user input.
Location
The Location class represents the location of a person or worker / public class Location The x coordinate of the location
Main
Entry point to the program.
ParserXml
The ParserXml class is responsible for parsing worker data from an XML file.
PermissionsDeniedException
This exception is thrown when a user does not have the necessary permissions to perform an action.
Person
The Person class represents a person and contains information about their birthday, height, passport ID, and location.
Position
The Position enumeration represents the different positions that an employee can hold within a company.
PrintFieldOfPerson
Command to print the Person data in ascending order by their name.
RemoveElementByID
The RemoveElementByID class represents a command to remove an element from the collection by its ID.
RemoveGreater
The RemoveGreater class represents a command to remove all elements from the collection that are greater than the specified element.
SaveCollection
The Show class represents a command that outputs all elements of the collection in string representation.
Show
Command
Sort
The Sort class represents a command to sort the collection in natural order.
Status
The Status enumeration represents the different statuses that an employee can have within a company.
UpdateByID
This command is used to update the value of a collection element whose id matches the specified one.
Worker
Represents a worker with a unique ID, name, coordinates, creation date, salary, position, status, and personal information.
WrongArgumentsException
This exception is thrown when the wrong number of arguments is provided to a method or function.
